snippet: The City of New York and Brookfield Properties will pay more than $230,000 to settle a lawsuit asserting that books and other property were damaged or destroyed when Zuccotti Park was cleared in 2011.
abstract: City of New York and Brookfield Properties will pay more than $230,000 to settle lawsuit that assered books and other property, belonging to members of Occupy Wall Street, were damaged or destroyed when Zuccotti Park was cleared in 2011.
lead_paragraph: The City of New York and Brookfield Properties will pay more than $230,000 to settle a lawsuit asserting that books and other property were damaged or destroyed when Zuccotti Park was cleared in 2011.

headline.seo: Occupy Wall Street Wins Suit Over Seizure of Library
headline.main: Suit Settled With Occupy Wall St. Over Seizure of Library at a Park
headline.print_headline: Suit Settled With Occupy Wall St. Over Seizure of Library at a Park
